<BaseLayout title="About" description="Stepan Zolotukhin — systems engineer working on ZINC, with a background in storage infrastructure, Linux systems, and AWS.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>I'm Stepan Zolotukhin. I'm a systems engineer. Right now I spend most of my time on GPU compute and local AI inference.</p>

  <p>I spent seven years building infrastructure for storage systems. For the past six years, I've worked at AWS on low-level systems problems across Linux kernels, userland, cross-compilation, glibc, and adjacent platform work.</p>

  <p>I'm building <a href="/zinc">ZINC</a>, an inference engine for AMD consumer GPUs that the mainstream AI stack does not support. It uses Zig and Vulkan compute shaders instead of ROCm or CUDA. The goal is to make a $500 GPU as useful for local LLM inference as hardware that costs 30x more.</p>

  <p>I write about the work here — how the GPU kernels are tuned, what the quantization tradeoffs look like, and the systems engineering decisions behind ZINC.</p>

